@startuml adapt-flow
!theme plain

title Adapt Flow

actor "User / CLI" as User
participant "Orchestrator" as Orch
participant "Claude API" as Claude
participant "TTS Provider" as TTS
participant "Image Provider" as Image
participant "Whisper" as Whisper
participant "FFmpeg" as FFmpeg

note over User
  User provides a finished story.
  The pipeline narrates it as-is
  and handles structure and visuals.
end note

User -> Orch: create(mode=adapt, input)

== Scene Splitting ==
Orch -> Claude: Split source text into scenes
Claude --> Orch: scene titles + text
Orch -> Orch: Write scene_NNN.md per scene

== Narration Flagging ==
Orch -> Claude: Flag narration issues\n(unpronounceable names, ambiguities)
Claude --> Orch: flags (if any)

== Image Prompts ==
Orch -> Claude: Generate image prompts\n(all scene prose)
Claude --> Orch: image prompt per scene

== Narration Prep ==
loop for each scene
  Orch -> Claude: Prepare text for spoken delivery
  Claude --> Orch: modified text + changelog
end

== TTS Generation ==
loop for each scene
  Orch -> TTS: Synthesize narration audio
  TTS --> Orch: audio bytes
  Orch -> Orch: Write scene_NNN.mp3
end

== Image Generation ==
loop for each scene
  Orch -> Image: Generate illustration\n(style_prefix + image_prompt)
  Image --> Orch: PNG image
  Orch -> Orch: Write scene_NNN.png
end

== Caption Generation ==
loop for each scene
  Orch -> Whisper: Transcribe audio
  Whisper --> Orch: word-level timestamps
  Orch -> Orch: Reconcile punctuation from prose
  Orch -> Orch: Write scene_NNN.json + .ass
end

== Video Assembly ==
loop for each scene
  Orch -> FFmpeg: Composite image + audio + captions
  FFmpeg --> Orch: scene_NNN.mp4
end
Orch -> FFmpeg: Concatenate with crossfades
FFmpeg --> Orch: final.mp4

Orch --> User: Done — final.mp4

@enduml
